<summary>
The <strong><c>ray()</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Functions">function</see> defines the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-path"><c>offset-path</c></see> line segment that an animated element can follow. The line segment is referred to as "ray". The ray begins from an <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/offset-position">offset-position</see> and extends in the direction of the specified angle. The length of a ray can be constrained by specifying a size and using the <c>contain</c> keyword.
</summary>
